What is the clique number of the following graph? 

Graph G: 
Vertices = {A, B, C, D, E}
Edges = {(A,B), (A,C), (B,C), (C,D), (C,E)}

Hint: A clique in a graph is a subset of vertices where every vertex is directly connected to every other vertex in the subset. The clique number of a graph is the size of the largest clique in that graph.
